25|$|The Continuous Electron <b>Beam</b> <b>Accelerator</b> Facility at Jefferson Lab, {{also called}} the Thomas Jefferson National Accelerator Facility, in Newport News, Virginia is one of 10 Department of Energy {{facilities}} doing research on gluons. The Virginia lab is competing with another facility on Long Island, New York, Brookhaven National Laboratory, for funds {{to build a new}} electron-ion collider.|$|E
